{"id":"3743","name":"Fling Spotify","tagline":"Change the device which is playing Spotify music","icon":"ios13 c4292093695 g59822","latest":"11716","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>Uses Spotify Connect to transfer current music playback from one device in your account to another.</p>\n<p>My first large shortcut, it may not be very useful for some people but I'm proud of it!</p>\n<p>Requires a Spotify Premium account. The first time you run the shortcut, it will guide you through the steps to register an API key, as well as authorize the application.</p>\n<p>For the first-time authorization, it uses a small website that gets the response from Spotify and gives it to the shortcut (Spotify is not able to call back shortcuts directly). The page is <a href=\"https://oauth-proxy.netlify.com/?__shortcut=Fling%20Spotify\">https://oauth-proxy.netlify.com/?__shortcut=Fling%20Spotify</a>. It's completely static and the source code simple and freely inspectable. It doesn't send any information anywhere; and the information it handles can't be used by itself.</p>\n<p>Source for the shortcut and the proxy at <a href=\"https://github.com/cprecioso/Fling-Spotify.shortcut\">my GitHub</a></p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.2 - Oct. 21, 2019, 8:07 a.m.</strong></p><p>Fix update check</p>"}